		<article>
			<h1 class="storytitle"><a href="http://markos.gaivo.net/blog/?p=168" rel="bookmark">Mobile user interfaces</a></h1>

			<div class="post-text">
				<p>I&#8217;ve been working on Marela uploader for series60 phones (those with Python support) and have had a great fun discovering the world of user interfaces on mobile devices.</p>
<p>If you think there&#8217;s not enough space on your average web page, you really should try designing an interface for a device with stamp size screen with a resolution of <a href="http://www.c64.com/">Commodore 64</a> in full color mode (but luckily with far more colors) and input device that only kids could love. On top of that there&#8217;s a limited selection of existing UI controls to chose from and text can&#8217;t be too small to remain legible.</p>
<p>Still, I think the major problems have been solved and I&#8217;m maybe a day or so of development and a decent camera phone away from first working version. I&#8217;m hoping to get it done by this weekend, but realist in me keeps screaming: &#8220;Maybe next week!&#8221;</p>
			</div>

			<footer class="post-metadata">
				<ul>
